<HL>
   Who's News:
   J.P. Morgan's de Las Heras
   To Join Banco Santander
</HL>
<DATE>
04/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B9
</SO>
<CO>
   JPM WNEWS STD
</CO>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- J.P. Morgan &amp; Co.'s head of Latin America,
Gonzalo de Las Heras, resigned to take a senior job at Banco
Santander, Spain's second-largest bank.
   Mr. de Las Heras, 50 years old, will work on the bank's
international strategy, reporting to Chairman Emilio Botin.
In a statement, Mr. de Las Heras said, "I'm excited about the
scope of the projects Santander has asked me to tackle."
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Spanish-born Mr. de Las Heras joined Morgan in Madrid
in 1978 and soon rose to head its operations there. After
later moving to New York, Mr. de Las Heras played an
instrumental role in Mexico's initial debt-for-securities
swap arranged by Morgan in 1988.
