<HL>
   Business Brief -- Petroleum Helicopters Inc.:
   Industrial Equity (Pacific)
   Files to Raise Stake to 25%
</HL>
<DATE>
04/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   PHEL H.IEP A.BRY
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Industrial Equity (Pacific) Ltd., a Hong Kong investment
firm, said it filed with federal antitrust regulators to
raise its stake in Petroleum Helicopters Inc. to as much as
25%.
   In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Industrial
Equity (Pacific) also said it sent a letter to Petroleum
Helicopters Thursday saying it intended to seek board
representation. According to the filing, that request was
denied.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In New Orleans, John La Plante, secretary and treasurer of
Petroleum Helicopters, had no comment "at the present time,"
but he confirmed the company received the letter seeking
representation.
   In December, Industrial Equity (Pacific) said it raised
its stake in Petroleum Helicopters to the equivalent of 17%,
including an option to buy 12%.
   In the filing, Industrial Equity (Pacific) said it had
discussions with Petroleum Helicopters' management concerning
ways of maximizing long-term shareholder value and expects to
continue such talks.
   Petroleum Helicopters was quoted at $25.50 bid in
over-the-counter trading.
</TEXT>
