<LP>
   CHICAGO -- An Amoco Corp. unit signed a 10-year natural
gas transportation agreement with Natural Gas Pipeline Co. of
America, a unit of Occidental Petroleum Corp.'s Midcon Corp.
subsidiary.
   Under the agreement, Amoco Energy Trading Corp. can ship
as much as 250 million cubic feet a day of natural gas from
various sources in the middle of the continent to the Texas
and Louisiana Gulf Coast, where it would have access to
almost all major interstate pipelines to markets in the Gulf
Coast, Southeast and Northeast.
